note bottom of agent_service
Current use case split:
- pre-HITL A2UI shortcut
- planner-backed review gate
- unary/stream execution
- review approve/cancel ack
- approve는 immutable reviewed snapshot resume만 허용
- STREAM approve 결과는 task-scoped event stream 재구독으로 전달
end note

note bottom of orchestrator
Coordinator only:
- connect graph execution and fallback
- translate exceptions
- keep execution boundary thin
Not owner of:
- review gate
- persistence policy details
- A2UI product mapping
- 신규 agent registration
end note

note bottom of supervisor_execution_persistence_facade
Persistence facade pattern:
- single entrypoint for write scenarios
- chooses strategy by persistence command
- keeps services away from Redis/store details
- delegates write ordering to coordinator
- conversation/checkpoint write also go through this boundary
end note

note bottom of supervisor_read_facade
Read facade pattern:
- single entrypoint for read scenarios
- chooses query handler by read intent
- keeps services away from store-specific lookup details
- centralizes ownership/version/snapshot read policy
end note

note bottom of LifecycleService
Lifecycle service:
- lifecycle policy / read model boundary
- no direct Redis write
- write intent delegates to facade
end note

note bottom of GraphFactoryImpl
Current graph nodes:
- select
- invoke
- handoff_evaluate
- handoff_apply
- merge
- compose
Graph input:
- precomputed routing queue
- reviewed snapshot resume state
- handoff policy context
end note

note bottom of graph_execution_service
Execution boundary:
- load runtime state
- invoke graph
- publish progress
- request terminal persistence through facade
- update lifecycle through dedicated services
end note

note bottom of state_loader
Read-only restore boundary:
- builds restore request only
- actual store access goes through read facade/query layer
- no Redis write
end note

note bottom of task_facade
Read model boundary:
- delegates task read model lookup to read facade
- used by tasks/get, tasks/list, response shaping
- does not write Redis directly
end note

note bottom of ComposeImpl
Compose can emit:
- text events
- A2UI payload
- pre-HITL-only A2UI views are skipped in post-invoke compose
- progress/reasoning are never persisted as task payload
end note

note bottom of CompositeA2uiService
Current supported scope:
- product A2UI
- reservation A2UI
- pre-HITL input form A2UI
- post-invoke compose A2UI
Extension rule:
- 신규 agent 기본 등록은 yml + agent card
- raw payload/A2UI만 optional adapter
end note

